## What kind of change is this?

Bug fixes (non-breaking change which fixes an issue)

# Documentation changes needed?

My changes do not require a change to the project documentation.

# Testing

## Where should a reviewer start?

1. Review the package.json changes in packages/adapter-postgres/package.json
2. Verify the added files: schema.sql and seed.sql are included

2. Instantiate PostgresDatabaseAdapter
3. Call db.init()

5. Verify migrations run successfully

# Deploy Notes

After merging, a new package version will need to be published to npm to make the fix available to users.

title: Fix: character file plugins import error
body:
# Fix for Plugin Import Issues through Character file

# Relates to

# Risks
- Low risk - Changes only affect plugin import behavior
- Impacts community-published plugins without default exports
- No changes to core functionality or existing working plugins

# Background
## What does this PR do?

It was noticed while adding plugins to the character file, many plugins would fail and the agent would crash. This happened because the code is written to get default exports and many plugins are not doing so. They have named exports, which caused the imported plugin default to be undefined!  

Fixes plugin import mechanism to properly handle community-published plugins that don't use default exports. The changes:
- Add proper error handling for failed imports
- Support multiple plugin exports from a single file
- Maintain backward compatibility with default exports

## Type of Change
Bug fix - Resolves plugin import failures

# Documentation Impact
No changes are needed to project documentation as this fixes implementation details without changing the public API.

# Testing
## Where to start?
1. Start with loadCharacters() function in src/[file].ts
2. Focus on the plugin import logic changes
3. Check error handling improvements

## Testing Steps
1. Test with a plugin using the default export
   - Import should work as before
   - Verify plugin loads correctly

2. Test with community plugin (no default export)
   - Create a test plugin with named exports
   - Verify all valid plugins are imported
   - Check console logs for proper import tracking

3. Test with invalid plugin
   - Verify graceful error handling

# Discord Username
bchief#0

Looking forward to your review! Please let me know if you need any clarification.

title: chore(ci): add pnpm lockfile consistency check workflow
body:
# Relates to
N/A - Direct improvement to CI process

# Risks
Low - This is a new CI workflow that doesn't affect the production code.

# Background

## What does this PR do?
Currently, on the main branch, `pnpm install` fails to run due to pnpm-lock.yaml is not up to date with package.json.
This affects the user experience of those come to try Eliza for the first time, since they have to troubleshoot and decide to use `pnpm install --no-frozen-lockfile` to update the pnpm-lock file manually.

This repo adds a new GitHub Actions workflow that automatically checks if the pnpm lockfile is consistent with package.json files for each new PR created. When inconsistencies are found, it fails the PR check and provides clear instructions to contributors on how to resolve the issue.

## What kind of change is this?
Improvements (misc. changes to existing features)
- Adds new CI workflow to improve development process
- Helps prevent pnpm-lockfile related issues before PR gets merged to develop/main

# Documentation changes needed?
No need.

# Testing

## Where should a reviewer start?
1. Review the new workflow file: `.github/workflows/lockfile-check.yml`
2. Check the workflow configuration and error messages

## Detailed testing steps
1. Create a test PR with an outdated lockfile:
   - Modify a package.json file
   - Don't run pnpm install
   - Push changes
   - Verify the workflow fails and provides clear instructions
2. Update the lockfile:
   - Run `pnpm install --no-frozen-lockfile`
   - Commit and push the updated lockfile as a chore
   - Verify the workflow passes

# Deploy Notes
No special deployment needed - workflow will be active as soon as it's merged to the target branch.

## Database changes
None

## Deployment instructions
Standard GitHub Actions workflow deployment - no additional steps required.

## Discord username
jonathanesum

title: fix: remove legacy variables (XAI_MODEL,  XAI_API_KEY & IMAGE_GEN)
body:
# Relates to

This is a continuation of https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/pull/1930. These variables (XAI_MODEL,  XAI_API_KEY & IMAGE_GEN) are relics from legacy code that is no longer used. The only variable that was actually used is XAI_API_KEY for the Together API but it has its own api key variable so it's not actually needed at all. I also think it was creating confusion for some users thinking it was related to xAI, Grok or Twitter (also based on its location in env). I updated the docs/guides that include these variables but there are still a lot of translations that need to be updated. I did english and spanish.

# Risks

No risk, only 1 line of actual code was altered (removed). The rest is all docs and the env.example file.

# Background

## What does this PR do?

Removes unused variables

Fix or update
